# SSR / Hydration Safety

Hydration mismatches occur when the server-rendered HTML differs from the client VDOM on first mount. They appear as `Hydration class/node/style mismatch` warnings. Avoid all patterns below.

## Opt out of SSR for client-heavy pages

Auth-gated, non-public pages (editors, dashboards, settings) gain nothing from SSR and are prime sources of hydration bugs. Opt them out:

```ts
// ✅ pages/articles/edit/[id].vue, pages/messages/*.vue, etc.
definePageMeta({ ssr: false, ... })
```

## Never use v-if for responsive variants

`v-if` changes the DOM structure. Use CSS-only hiding instead so the DOM is identical on server and client.

```html
<!-- ❌ BAD — server renders Comment, client renders button -->
<button v-if="!isMobile">Desktop</button>
<button v-else>Mobile</button>

<!-- ✅ GOOD — same DOM on server + client, CSS controls visibility -->
<button class="hidden sm:inline-flex">Desktop</button>
<button class="inline-flex sm:hidden">Mobile</button>
```

## Guard client-only :style with a hydrated ref

Styles based on browser values (keyboard height, window size, scroll) are unknown at SSR time. Return `undefined` until after mount.

```ts
const hydrated = ref(false)
onMounted(() => { hydrated.value = true })

// ✅ returns undefined on server (no inline style), applies after mount
const dynamicStyle = computed(() =>
  hydrated.value && someClientValue.value > 0
    ? { paddingBottom: `${someClientValue.value}px` }
    : undefined
)
```

```html
<!-- Static fallback via CSS class; dynamic override only after hydration -->
<div class="pb-[4.5rem]" :style="dynamicStyle">
```

## Never bind browser APIs outside onMounted

```ts
// ❌ BAD — window is undefined on server
const height = ref(window.innerHeight)

// ✅ GOOD
const height = ref(0)
onMounted(() => { height.value = window.innerHeight })
```

## Use <ClientOnly> for truly browser-only components

```html
<!-- Maps, charts, third-party widgets that can't SSR -->
<ClientOnly>
  <MyMapComponent />
</ClientOnly>
```
